text.__SUMMARY__: Uluops is an extinct genus of turtle from the Late Jurassic Morrison Formation. The type species is Uluops uluops.
text.References: K. Carpenter and R. T. Bakker. 1990. A new latest Jurassic vertebrate fauna, from the highest levels of the Morrison Formation at Como Bluff, Wyoming, with comments on Morrison biochronology. Part II. A new baenid turtle. Hunteria 2(6):3-4
